AI Product Management Portfolio

A collection of AI PM projects built to demonstrate product thinking, technical depth, and AI-specific design judgment.

About Me

I am transitioning into AI Product Management, with a background in data analytics and business intelligence. My work sits at the intersection of data, AI features, and the real-world users who depend on them.

These projects are built from genuine problems I have encountered — not hypothetical case studies.

Projects

01 · Copilot Readiness Analyzer for Power BI
Status: PRD Complete · Build In Progress

A developer-facing tool that scans Power BI semantic models, scores their Copilot compatibility, and gives analysts a prioritized remediation path. Built to solve a real problem: ~300 legacy reports across a regional organization that Copilot cannot effectively reason over.

Key PM skills demonstrated:
- Enterprise AI product thinking
- Human-in-the-loop design
- Phased scoping (audit → auto-remediation)
- AI-specific risk and trust considerations

[View Project →](./01-powerbi-copilot-readiness/)

02 · Zebra AI-Inspired Analytics Tool
Status: Coming Soon

An internal analytics tool inspired by Zebra AI — designed to bring natural language querying and AI-assisted insight generation to a regional organization's data estate.

[View Project →](./02-zebra-ai-inspired/)

How I Work

Each project in this portfolio follows the same structure:

1. Problem Statement — grounded in a real user pain, not invented
2. PRD — full product requirements document with AI-specific considerations
3. Practical Build — working prototype or technical architecture
4. Retrospective — what I learned, what I would do differently

